                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="DonationNote"/>
                           <locus target="#69v" facs="0072"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ መልእክተ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወመልእክተ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ ዕብራውያን። ዘወሀበ፡ ፍሬ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወልዱ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ለቅዱስ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ በቅድመ፡ ነጋድያን፡ ፯። 
                              ራይስ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወቀሲስ፡ ዘርአ፡ ልዑል። ወቀሲስ፡ ያዕቆብ። ወቀሲስ፡ ተክለ፡ ብርሃን። ወተንሥአ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ አቡነ፡ ኤዮስጣቴዎስ። ወዓሥራተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወልዱ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ 
                              ከመ፡ ትኩኖ፡ መድኃኒ<supplied reason="omitted">ተ</supplied>፡ ነፍሱ። ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ በአፉሆሙ፡ ለጴጥሮስ፡ ወለጳውሎስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወአሜን።
                           </q>
                           <note>The note states that <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11225FereMi">Fǝre Mikāʾel</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11208HouseTakla">spiritual son of ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot</persName>, 
                              donated the book to the monastery of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0302SanStefano">Santo Stefano dei Mori</placeName>. 
                              The donation took place in the presence of seven pilgrims, i.e.: <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10372Yohanne">
                                 <roleName type="title">rāyǝs</roleName> 
                              Yoḥannǝs</persName> 
                              (cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/2FPWFRHU"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Fiaccadori1989Aethiopica"/><title level="a">Aethiopica minima</title><title level="j">Quaderni Utinensi</title><author><forename>Gianfranco</forename><surname>Fiaccadori</surname></author><date>1989</date><biblScope unit="volume">7 (13/14)</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">145-164</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Fiaccadori1989Aethiopica</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Fiaccadori1989Aethiopica</note><citedRange unit="item">160 n. 17</citedRange></bibl>),  
                              priest <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11227ZaraLe">Zarʾa Lǝʿul</persName>, 
                              priest <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11228Yaeqob">Yāʿqob</persName>, priest Takla Bǝrhān (presumably the same as <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11229TaklaBe">Takla Bǝrhān Walda Qʷayyaṣā</persName>), 
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11230TanseaK">Tanśǝʾa Krǝstos</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11207Ewostateans">spiritual son of ʾabuna ʾEyosṭātewos</persName>, 
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11231AsrataM">ʿAśrāta Māryām</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11232HouseSam">spiritual son of  ʾabuna Sāmuʾel of Wāldǝbbā</persName>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 5 | Aethiop.</q> is written on the cover, together with the coat of arms of pope <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7893PiusIX">Pius IX</persName>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#Ir" facs="0001"/>
                           <desc>A remark "<q xml:lang="it">Tratta della conuersione di S. Pietro sorsa ex Actis Apostolor<supplied reason="explanation">um</supplied>
                              </q>" was written by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11238Contelori">Felice Contelori</persName>. The note is erased. 
                              Other notes are written in a later hand (presumably of the <date>17th century</date>): <q>10</q> (previous shelfmark of the manuscript, 
                              then erased); the titles of the work in Latin<q xml:lang="la">Epistola Petri. 1. f. 1 | 2 da f. 11 | Epistola s. Iohannis. 1. f. 17 | 2<hi rend="apices">a</hi>. f. 27. | Epistola Iudae. f. 39. | Epistola ad Ebraeos. f. 41. | N° 5</q>". 
                              The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">5. Aethiop.</q> is also written on the same leaf in a <date>18th-century</date>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <locus target="#17r" facs="0019"/>
                           <desc>
                              <q xml:lang="la">S. Io Chrysostomus</q> is written in a <date>16th-century</date> hand and erased.
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>Doodles on <locus from="62" to="65r"/> and on <locus target="#66r #68v #69v"/>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>Corrections, additions and the chapter numbers according to the Latin Vulgata have been inserted on the left margin of many leaves by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9286Tasfase">Tasfā Ṣǝyon</persName>. 
                              The same scholar also numbered the pages containing the text to be printed in his edition of the New Testament: <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/8UWD3FCM"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Petrus1548Test"/><title level="m">Testamentum Novum: Cum Epistola Pauli Ad Hebreos tantum, cum concordantijs Evangelistarum Eusebii &amp; numeratione omnium verborum eorundem. Missale cum benedictione incensi cerae et c. Alphabetum in lingua ግእዝ፡ gheez, idest libera quia a nulla alia originem duxit, &amp; vulgo dicitur Chaldea, Quae omnia Fr. Petrus Ethyops auxilio piorum sedente Paulo. III. Pont. MAx. &amp; Claudio illius regni Imperatore imprimi curavit</title><author><t:name xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Petrus Ethyops</t:name></author><pubPlace>Romae</pubPlace><publisher>Impensis Petri Comos Ethiopis, Valerius Doricus</publisher><date>1548</date><note type="url">https://books.google.de/books?id=KPNa9Mc5gjYC</note></bibl>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        </list>
                  </additions>
            
